      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm honestly just so exhausted with this. sitting in this office doing data entry while knowing that the entire framework for the 2022 maritime trade agreement was actually built on the clauses i drafted back in '19. it's like they just scrubbed my name from every single primary document and replaced it with agency handles. i feel like i'm losing my mind because no one else sees how obvious the breadcrumbs are in the policy footnotes. help me make sense of this, please. i can't be the only one who notices how they've covered it up.",
